remind me when I am really supposed to be impressed, k?<br>
<br>
I prefer not to use darkness unless I have to.  In a LDoN, I cast jolt one time, then snare if it doesn't get me agro IMMEDIATELY (and I almost NEVER use my snare).  I have used my voice line before, but I find that it is more a hassle than help if I am using it on myself.  The terror line seems to work MUCH better if I have someone else tanking and I cast it on them.<br>
Perhaps that's why the spell was created with that ability (/ponder).<br>
<br>
As for the darkness line, I did use it once and had to chain cast clinging/fear to keep agro.  Sure, it worked, took up an extra spell slot (fear), required me to chain cast it, and did NO damage for all the casting since it was ALWAYS resisted.  With one time on Terror, I kept agro on almost every engagement.  Since I don't acatually know the numbers on clinging, I would assume it is lower.  Considering the terror line seems to hold it with one cast, I'll stick with what works.  I will leave a snare up that WORKS, in case I need it.<br>
What DOESN'T work is relying on my melee DPS to hold agro.  If Clinging works for you, great... use it.  I like nuking while I am fighting, so spending my spell casts chain castng darkness spells is a waste.  Especially when I can get it done with one cast (or 4 if I am having fun) before I even break mez.<br>
<br>
Also, I don't like waiting for taunt to pop.  If the mob turns on a caster, I like having my taunt ready to go... so wasting it on a mezzed mob would be a little counter-productive.  Especially when I have so many other options open to me.<br>
<br>
